title: 820-01700 no power
message:
Arrived with liquid damage and a short on PPBUS_G3H. Injected 1v and found u7660 getting hot. Replaced and short is gone.

PPBUS is 12.33V now bu board stuck at 5v 0.04amps

What should be checked next?

title: 820-01700 no power
message:
Compare diode mode readings on all coils with good board.
Don't forget L9080/580.

See if DFU helps...

title: 820-01700 no power
message:
checking diode mode on L7660 found U7800 shorted.

Replaced U7800, short is gone but have a pure short on PP1V8_SLPS2R.

When injecting voltage only the T2 gets hot.  Sound like a shorted T2 now??

title: 820-01700 no power
message: If T2 heats with so low voltage, no other reason...
